# VIF Trading System — Complete Architecture Map

**Last updated:** 2026-05-11

**Upload this file to Claude Desktop or Claude.ai browser to give Claude instant full-system context.**

---

## 1. Claude Code Agents (`.claude/agents/`)

These are reusable agent personas Claude assumes in chat sessions. Invoke with `/agent-name`.

| Agent | Purpose | Python Backing | Load-bearing? |
|-------|---------|-----------------|---------------|
| `orchestrator-coordinator` | Master pipeline controller; delegates to 5 different analysis modes | `agents/orchestrator.py` | YES — runs all schedules |
| `vif-analyst` | Watchlist VIF signal generation (BUY/SELL/HOLD) | `agents/watchlist_watcher.py` | YES — primary analysis |
| `weekend-catalyst-analyst` | Monday morning briefing with macro themes, earnings, sector rotation | `agents/weekend_catalyst_agent.py` | YES — weekend pipeline |
| `swing-trade-screener` | 5 swing setup types ranked by R:R ratio, 2-4 week timeframe | `scripts/swing_trade_screener_v2.py` | YES — part of daily pipeline |
| `catalyst-monitor` | Government policy, regulatory decisions, earnings dates, K4 kill switches | `scripts/catalyst_analysis.py` | YES — first step of premarket |
| `indicator-engine` | Shared technical indicator reference (RSI, MACD, BB, EMA, ATR, Gamma Regime, K1–K6) | `agents/indicators.py` | NO (informational, not in pipeline) |
| `market-researcher` | Ad-hoc Q&A for VIF signals, macro catalysts, technical levels | `agents/claude_research_agent.py` | NO (manual CLI only) |
| `report-builder` | HTML report generation from raw JSON data | `scripts/html_report_generator.py` + `scripts/generate_vif_master_report.py` | YES — creates final output |
| `cost-analyzer` | API cost tracking, budget analysis, token usage | `scripts/check_usage.py` | NO (manual monitoring) |
| `feature-extractor` | Meta-tool: extracts core logic from GitHub repos | None (pure Claude Code) | NO (GitHub workflow only) |
| `integration-planner` | Meta-tool: maps extracted features to VIF system | None (pure Claude Code) | NO (GitHub workflow only) |
| `repo-scanner` | Meta-tool: scans GitHub repositories for reusable code | None (pure Claude Code) | NO (GitHub workflow only) |

