## 3. Python Agents in `agents/`

These are the actual runtime executors. Invoked by `schedule_daily.py` and orchestrator.

| Script | Role | Called By | Load-bearing? |
|--------|------|-----------|---------------|
| `orchestrator.py` | Master pipeline controller; runs subprocesses for each analysis type | `schedule_daily.py` every slot | **YES** — Entry point for all automation |
| `orchestrator_swarm.py` | **Phase 3:** Swarm-based orchestration (LRAgent + LatentMAS routing) | Phase 3 integration | **YES** — Next-gen coordinator |
| `finviz_screener_agent.py` | **Phase 3:** FinViz Discovery Screener (19 custom screeners) | `schedule_daily.py` 07:30 | **YES** — Institutional discovery |
| `finviz_orchestrator_coordinator.py` | **Phase 3:** FinViz swarm integration layer | orchestrator_swarm finviz_screen pipeline | YES — Swarm routing |
| `external_alpha_auditor.py` | **Phase 4.5:** GitHub + HF MCP wrapper (low-confidence research audit) | Critic agent when confidence < 55% | Soft — Enhancement layer |
| `watchlist_watcher.py` | Core VIF analyzer; loads watchlists, fetches OHLCV, batches to Claude for signals | Orchestrator premarket/afterhours/full | **YES** — Primary analysis |
| `weekend_catalyst_agent.py` | Fetches earnings, momentum, macro themes; generates Monday briefing JSON | Orchestrator weekend/full | **YES** — Weekend reporting |
| `indicators.py` | Shared IndicatorEngine class; computes RSI, MACD, BB, EMA, ATR, Gamma Regime, K1–K6 | Orchestrator `run_single_ticker()` + imported by skills | Soft (not used in main pipeline) |
| `claude_research_agent.py` | Interactive CLI for manual research queries; takes --query and --model args | Manual only, never scheduled | NO — Convenience tool |
| `report_ui_agent.py` | **ARCHIVED** — Markdown fallback (never triggered by pipeline) | — | NO — Dead path |

**Technical Debt Note:** `watchlist_watcher.py` has its own inline `compute_rsi()` and does NOT use `indicators.py`. If you change RSI logic in `indicators.py`, the main pipeline is unaffected. Fix: import from `indicators.py` instead (future session, needs testing).

